begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves and talked about where we live now and where we lived before. We went through a little of our past history even back to where we were born or went to school, etc.
middle_memory_text: We moved into talking about Covid and how that has effected our communities and our friends. She shared some shocking info on how the people of Detroit have been effected.
end_memory_text: We talked about bigger issues like where to find our passion, how to find passion in work or if not work, ensure that work doesn't encroach on personal time so much that we can't follow our passion outside of it. Talked about developing nations compared to what is happening here at home. Ended with a few final good thoughts.
rest_of_day_open: I will go back to what I normally do but I will also be thinking about what we just discussed regarding work balance. I tend to let it creep and I'll make an effort to work effectively enough to get the work done in a bounded time frame which leaves time for more meaningful activity.
critical_positive: I love to talk with people who are engaged in the world in a positive way. My discussion partner was very interested in people and making things better yet was not an angry person. She was obviously very intelligent and had the confidence to express herself well. I could have talked much longer.
critical_negative: I was self conscious about how I come across in a video. While I am talking to people for work throughout the day, I am not on video calls, thus do not see how I look when engaging. I caught a glimpse or two and found that I am over-emotive at times.

begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves and where we were. We then talked about COVID-19 for a bit, about how it impacted our respective regions and our acquaintances.
middle_memory_text: The discussion of COVID-19 led to me talking about living in Detroit and about how very poor and bereft some areas are, to the point of having residences without running water. We talked a bit about the differences between the US and other countries and various standards of living.
end_memory_text:
She talked about an area outside of Dallas that she thought was similar to parts of Detroit and about a man who moved there to start a farm to provide improved food access and income for that community. She also talked about a trip to Nepal, and sharing photos with the children in the community outside of Dallas as some perspective on their lives. 

I forgot to mention that between the beginning and middle of the conversation, we talked about work and how millenials were taught to follow their dreams and about how that often translated to professional work. We discussed that that is not a practical way to run an economy, and we talked about how Americans work so many hours that their only chance to really follow their dreams often is through work, and how if we worked less and allowed for more leisure ,we might be able to have more fulfilled hobbies and overall lives.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of this week is going to be good. I'm working hard to have a good mental health week, so I am not drinking until the weekend and every day, I am trying to be a little bit active. I am also off social media, so that helps. I don't have many specific plans, but I will be hosting a very small (4 people) birthday wine tasting for one of my closest friends.
critical_positive: Both Pam and I share some demographics. Despite our age difference, we are both white women from affluent backgrounds with lots of opportunity. That helped because we have similar social norms, and so our conversation began with basically no awkwardness. We also share a passion for helping people and have had experiences with people with less privilege than ourselves, so we have been humbled by those experiences.
critical_negative: There really wasn't much that didn't work. We both seemed to talk almost an equal amount, and I felt heard and understood by her as I think she did me. I didn't necessarily agree with 100% of what she said, but we were able to speak fairly honestly and openly for talking with a stranger. I think that the things we shared helped make the conversation go smoothly, and it was sincerely interesting for both of us.
